    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for the expansion. it's getting better. \n\ni just ran this draft through the audit tool's previewer and it's flagging a few things. it says some of the requirements seem \"thinly covered\" because the terms are appearing in very dense, single sentences rather than being integrated into broader operational explanations. \n\ncould you go deeper into the specifics? for example, talk more about the role of the data protection officer, how we manage storage limitations/retention, and the actual mechanics of how a breach notification would work in practice. \n\ni'm really stressing here—don't just add more terms or make the sentences longer for the sake of it. the tool's score is secondary; if the memo is just a list of buzzwords, the partner will reject it immediately. i need you to provide actual, actionable, detailed workflows that use these terms naturally in a professional context. \n\nmake it a robust, long-form memo that the compliance team can actually use as a manual.",
